NAME
       bal connector sdk - Generate and maintain Ballerina connectors from Java
       SDKs.

SYNOPSIS
       bal connector sdk analyze <sdk-ref> <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk pipeline <sdk-ref> <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk generate <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk connector <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk fix-code <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk fix-report-only <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk generate-tests <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk generate-examples <output-dir> [options...]
       bal connector sdk generate-docs <output-dir> [options...]

DESCRIPTION
       Analyze Java SDKs, generate API specifications and intermediate
       representations, generate Ballerina connector code, and run
       AI-assisted code fixing, test generation, example generation, and
       documentation generation.

       The <sdk-ref> argument accepts a dataset key resolved from
       test-jars/<dataset-key>.jar and test-jars/<dataset-key>-javadoc.jar,
       or a Maven coordinate in the form group:artifact or
       group:artifact:version.

COMMANDS
       analyze
            Analyze a Java SDK from a dataset key or Maven coordinate and
            write SDK metadata under the output root.

       pipeline
            Run the full Java SDK connector workflow: SDK analysis, API
            specification and IR generation, connector code generation,
            code fixing, example generation, test generation, and
            documentation generation.

       generate
            Generate the API specification and intermediate representation
            from SDK analyzer metadata produced by the analyze command.

       connector
            Generate Ballerina connector artifacts (client, types, and
            native adaptor) from SDK metadata, IR, and API specification.

       fix-code
            Fix Java native adapter and Ballerina compilation errors in an
            SDK-generated connector.

       fix-report-only
            Run code fixer diagnostics for an SDK-generated connector
            without applying fixes. Reports remaining errors only.

       generate-tests
            Generate live integration tests for an SDK-generated connector.

       generate-examples
            Generate AI-assisted Ballerina examples for an SDK-generated
            connector.

       generate-docs
            Generate all README documentation for an SDK-generated
            connector.

OPTIONS
       sources=<path>
            Path to a sources JAR or extracted source directory for SDK
            analysis.

       include-packages=<packages>
            Comma-separated Java packages to restrict SDK analysis to.

       exclude-packages=<packages>
            Comma-separated Java packages to exclude from SDK analysis.

       max-depth=<n>
            Maximum dependency traversal depth during SDK analysis.

       methods-to-list=<n>
            Maximum number of SDK methods to include in analysis output.

       --fix-iterations=<n>
            Maximum code fixer iterations. The default is 3.

       include-deprecated
            Include deprecated SDK methods during analysis.

       include-internal
            Include SDK classes or methods that would otherwise be treated
            as internal.

       include-non-public
            Include non-public SDK classes or methods.

       no-thinking, --no-thinking
            Disable extended LLM reasoning mode during specification
            generation.

       --fix-code
            Run the full code fixing phase. Enabled by default in pipeline.

       --fix-report-only
            Run code fixer diagnostics without applying all fixes.

       --skip-fix
            Skip the code fixing phase.

       --skip-tests
            Skip SDK live test generation.

       --generate-examples, --skip-examples
            Run or skip example generation.

       --generate-docs, --skip-docs
            Run or skip documentation generation.

       yes, --yes, -y
            Auto-confirm pipeline checkpoints and prompts.

       quiet, --quiet, -q
            Reduce log output.

       verbose, --verbose, -v
            Show detailed diagnostic output.

EXAMPLES
       Analyze a Java SDK using a dataset key.
           $ bal connector sdk analyze s3-2.4.0 ./out

       Analyze a Java SDK using a Maven coordinate.
           $ bal connector sdk analyze \
                 com.example:example-sdk:1.2.3 ./out

       Analyze with package filtering and a sources JAR.
           $ bal connector sdk analyze s3-2.4.0 ./out \
                 include-packages=com.example.client sources=./src.jar

       Run the full SDK connector pipeline.
           $ bal connector sdk pipeline s3-2.4.0 ./out \
                 --fix-iterations=3

       Run the pipeline skipping tests and documentation.
           $ bal connector sdk pipeline s3-2.4.0 ./out \
                 --skip-tests --skip-docs

       Generate tests for an SDK-generated connector workspace.
           $ bal connector sdk generate-tests ./out
